861238497.text: "Here, we observed that : 1) gender differences existed in myocardial STAT3 activation and SOCS3 expression following I/R; 2) depletion of endogenous testosterone significantly increased activation of myocardial STAT3 and SOCS3 in male hearts, whereas blockade of testosterone receptor only increased SOCS3 levels in males subjected to I/R; 3) Administration of exogenous testosterone to castrated male and female hearts decreased their STAT3 activity and SOCS3 level."
